history.content: Probably EE149. CS162 is more heavyweight in terms of the computer systems that you will learn and doesn't really apply to robotics especially if you are already familiar with ROS from the 106 series. That being said, CS162 is the more useful class overall and the design patterns you learn in that class can be useful for the programmatic aspects of robotics, and even if it isn't, extremely useful in nearly any software engineering related pursuit you choose.

Hi! I am planning for future semesters and I have one slot to fill. I am considering doing graduate study or a job related to robotics and have taken EECS106 series, CS188 and CS189 and will take 182 next. So I am wondering which one is gonna be more useful for robotics, EECS 149 or CS162?
I have all the prereqs but not EE16B, is that gonna be a issue in terms of enrolling?
history.subject: EE149 or CS162 for robotics
